---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What is Writ?',
    a: 'Writ is a lightweight, always-ready text editor that lives in your system tray. Press a global hotkey to summon it, type, dismiss. It autosaves everything locally, so you never lose a thought.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How is it different from VS Code or Obsidian?',
    a: 'Writ is not a code editor or a knowledge base. It is a scratchpad for quick notes, snippets, and drafts. It opens instantly, disappears just as fast, and stays out of your way. Think of it as the text editor equivalent of Spotlight.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where is my data stored?',
    a: 'Everything is stored locally in a single SQLite database in your app data directory. There is no cloud sync, no telemetry, and nothing leaves your machine. You can back it up, move it, or delete it like any other file.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is Writ free and open source?',
    a: 'Yes. Writ is MIT licensed. The source is on GitHub, and contributions are welcome.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Which platforms are supported?',
    a: 'macOS (Apple Silicon and Intel), Windows x64, and Linux (.AppImage and .deb). Built on Tauri v2, SolidJS, and CodeMirror 6.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it signed and notarized?',
    a: 'Not yet. On macOS, right-click the app and choose Open on first launch. On Windows, SmartScreen may ask for confirmation. Code signing is on the roadmap for v0.2.',
  },
];
---

<section class="section" id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <header class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 id="faq-heading">Common questions</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((item, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item" open={i === 0}>
          <summary>
            <span>{item.q}</span>
            <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p>{item.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .faq-item {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition:
      box-shadow var(--duration-base) var(--ease-out),
      border-color var(--duration-base) var(--ease-out);
  }
  .faq-item[open] {
    border-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--accent) 24%, var(--border));
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow-hover);
  }
  .faq-item summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--foreground);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }
  .faq-item summary:hover {
    background: var(--muted);
  }
  .chev {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    transition: transform 0.2s var(--ease-out);
    display: inline-flex;
  }
  .faq-item[open] .chev {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 1.25rem 1.1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
  }
</style>
